Author: StressedCookie
Text: I over-exercised for a week then my body just wanted to rest. I haven't had the energy or willpower to do my morning routine for 2 days now. I feel guilty.   I went to the gym yesterday, finished starving and feeling like I burned all the bread I binged, only to have my mum invite me to a dinner that I can't decline for social etiquette.  God, I'm pretty sure I can't scream in front of them "I DONT WANT TO EAT LEAVE ME ALONE STOP NEEDING ME TO EAT WITH YOU BC IF SOCIAL NORMS. IM SUFFERING ENOUGH WITH MYSELF."

Author: Aleph0-4
Text: Yeah that's another thing non-disordered people don't understand. Back when she didn't understand, my mum would suggest I exercise instead of purging by vomiting... great. Now not only do I feel bad about binging, I feel bad about not having the willpower to exercise.
